    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n6790" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὄμνῡμι, ὀμνύω</span></b> , imp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὄμνυθι, ὀμνυέτω</span>, ipf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὤμνυε</span>, fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὀμοῦμαι,
            -εῖται</span>, aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὤμοσα,
            ὄμὁσ̓σα</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">take oath, swear;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὅρκον</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινί</span>, or <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πρός τινα</span>),
            <i><span class="en">Il. 3.279</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 14.331</span></i>; foll. by inf., also w. acc. of the person or
          thing in whose name, or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">by</span> whom or which, the oath is
          taken, <i><span class="en">Il. 14.271</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 15.40</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
